# UI catalog governance

Policy: `docs/adr/0006-ui-catalog-governance.md`. Density: `hogar-pro-ui-density.mdc`.

## Sources of truth

| Layer | Artifact |
|-------|----------|
| Visual patterns | Storybook (`canonical` stories) |
| Per-route contract | `frontend/docs/views/*.md` |
| Index | `frontend/docs/component-inventory.md` |
| Allowed forks | `frontend/docs/ui-exceptions.md` |

## Story class

- **canonical** — use in product (or elevate product to match).
- **reference** — mock/visual only; never wire as-is; extract look into a data-driven canonical component when adopting.

## Reuse / promote

- Prefer existing canonical components over new ones.
- Page-only composition may stay in `pages/` without a story.
- New reusable UI → component + story + inventory row in the same work unit.
- Same pattern in **3+** places (or both Hogar and PRO) → promote to Storybook.

## Agent modes

- **Audit / polish apply:** Storybook canonical → frontend (`ui-design-governance`).
- **Drift sync:** frontend → Storybook when product led (`ui-storybook-sync`).

## Do not

- Ship a second visual language for the same pattern without an exceptions row + exit criteria.
- Create SpecKit features only to track inventory/views.
- Use per-exception ADRs (use `ui-exceptions.md`).
